<article class="article">
  <h2>How an SWP works</h2>
  <p>A systematic withdrawal plan redeems a fixed amount from your mutual fund investment every month. Whatever remains stays invested and continues to compound. The corpus therefore runs a race between withdrawals draining it and returns replenishing it. If your annual withdrawals stay below the corpus's earnings, the balance grows forever; above that, it depletes on a schedule this calculator computes month by month.</p>

  <h2>The break-even withdrawal</h2>
  <div class="formula">Perpetual monthly withdrawal ≈ Corpus × r / 12</div>
  <p>At an 8% return, a ₹50 lakh corpus earns about ₹33,300 a month on average — withdraw less than that and your corpus is effectively perpetual (though market volatility means real-world outcomes vary around this average, especially in the early years).</p>

  <h2>Worked example</h2>
  <p>₹50,00,000 corpus, ₹30,000 monthly withdrawal, 8% p.a. return: the withdrawal (7.2% of corpus per year) is below the 8% earning rate, so the balance actually keeps rising while paying you ₹3.6 lakh a year. Raise the withdrawal to ₹45,000 and the corpus depletes in about 17.6 years after paying out roughly ₹95 lakh — nearly twice the starting amount, thanks to returns earned along the way.</p>

  <h2>How to use this calculator</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Enter your corpus, planned monthly withdrawal and expected return.</li>
    <li>If the balance never falls, the calculator reports the corpus as lasting 50+ years.</li>
    <li>Pair with the <a href="/fire-calculator/">FIRE calculator</a> to first size the corpus you need, then test withdrawal plans here.</li>
  </ul>
</article>

<script>
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
  var MAX_MONTHS = 600;
  function recalc() {
    var p = CM.val('p'), wd = CM.val('w'), r = CM.val('r') / 1200;
    if (p <= 0 || wd <= 0) return;
    var bal = p, mths = 0, totalWd = 0;
    var labels = ['Y0'], series = [p], rows = [];
    var yearWd = 0;
    while (bal > 0 && mths < MAX_MONTHS) {
      bal = bal * (1 + r);
      var take = Math.min(wd, bal);
      bal -= take; totalWd += take; yearWd += take;
      mths++;
      if (mths % 12 === 0 || bal <= 0) {
        var y = Math.ceil(mths / 12);
        labels.push('Y' + y); series.push(bal);
        rows.push([y, CM.inr(yearWd), CM.inr(bal)]);
        yearWd = 0;
      }
    }
    var never = bal > 0;
    CM.set('out-lasts', never ? '50+ years' : CM.num(mths / 12, 1) + ' years');
    CM.set('out-lasts-sub', never ? 'withdrawal is below what the corpus earns — it never depletes at this rate' : 'until the corpus is exhausted');
    CM.set('out-wd', CM.inr(totalWd));
    CM.set('out-rate', CM.num(wd * 12 / p * 100, 1) + '%');

    CM.lineChart('chart-bal', labels, [{ label: 'Corpus balance', data: series, role: '--s1', fill: true }]);
    CM.table('sched-out', ['Year', 'Withdrawn', 'Balance'], rows);
  }
  CM.bind(['p', 'w', 'r'], recalc);
});
</script>
